  "prompt": "Which book changed your life the most?",
  "response": "I don't have personal experiences or emotions, but I can suggest some books that are often cited as life-changing by many readers. For example:\n\n1. **\"The Alchemist\" by Paulo Coelho** - This novel explores themes of destiny, dreams, and personal legend, inspiring many to pursue their passions.\n\n2. **\"Man's Search for Meaning\" by Viktor Frankl** - Frankl\u2019s reflections on his experiences in Nazi concentration camps and the pursuit of meaning in life have profoundly impacted many readers.\n\n3. **\"To Kill a Mockingbird\" by Harper Lee** - This classic addresses serious themes of racial injustice and moral growth, leaving a lasting impression on generations of readers.\n\n4. **\"The Power of Now\" by Eckhart Tolle** - This spiritual guide encourages living in the present moment and has helped many find peace and clarity in their lives.\n\nDo any of these resonate with you?",
